{
  "texts": [
    "It requires a clear procedural framework to evaluate when and how policies should be revised -grounded in empirical evidence, ethical principles, and inclusive stakeholder dialogue.",
    "This adaptive approach acknowledges that disinformation is a moving target and must be governed as a continuously evolving sociotechnical risk, not a one-time legislative challenge.",
    "By embracing regulatory agility, policymakers can strike a balance between fostering innovation and safeguarding democratic discourse in an age of algorithmic manipulation.",
    "-Promote cognitive resilience and digital literacy campaigns about disinformation risks.",
    "-Mandate bias audits and diverse dataset requirements for AI training -Develop international cooperation mechanisms for AI regulation enforcement."
  ]
}